Eiffage, Saint Gobain, Thales, Valeo: French Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r t h e   F o u r c a d e   a n d   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-02-25T05:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/eiffage-saint-gobain-thales-valeo-french-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in France. Symbols are in parentheses after company names and
prices are from the previous close.  France’s benchmark  CAC 40 Index  dropped for a fourth day,
losing 0.1 percent to 4,009.64 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Paris.
The broader SBF-120 Index slid 0.1 percent to 2,991.80.    Eiffage SA  (FGR FP): France’s third-largest construction
company estimated sales this year will rise 3 percent to 13.7
billion euros. Eiffage fell 0.8 percent to 40.35 euros.  Cie. de Saint-Gobain SA (SGO FP): Europe’s biggest supplier
of building materials said it won’t rush the initial public
offering of a minority stake of its packaging unit if market
conditions aren’t appropriate. Saint-Gobain gained 0.3 percent
to 40.78 euros.    Thales SA  (HO FP): Europe’s largest defense-electronics
producer said its net loss shrank to 45 million euros last year
and it expects to “swiftly return to profitability.” Thales
rose 0.2 percent to 26.64 euros.    Valeo SA  (FR FP): France’s second-largest auto-parts
supplier posted a full-year profit on an Asian-led recovery in
auto demand, beating analysts’ expectations and its own
forecasts. Valeo fell 2.8 percent to 40.82 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
